WEBVTT

00:56.882 --> 00:58.667
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

02:31.281 --> 02:33.370
[HORNETS BUZZING]

02:47.558 --> 02:49.604
[SLOW DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

02:53.173 --> 02:55.262
[HORNETS BUZZING]

03:00.049 --> 03:02.094
[DRAMATIC MUSIC BUILDS]

03:04.445 --> 03:06.490
- [MUSIC STOPS]
- [BIRDS CHIRPING]

03:26.510 --> 03:28.208
That's them in there
just like that?

03:29.600 --> 03:30.645
Just like that.

03:32.037 --> 03:33.996
I wouldn't go in there
for a day or two.

03:35.127 --> 03:36.651
Heard the expression
kick the hornet's nest?

03:37.434 --> 03:38.653
I'll stay right here.
Thank you.

03:39.262 --> 03:40.916
Those things
scare me to death.

03:40.916 --> 03:42.309
They been killing
my honey bees.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.833
A few days unchecked,

03:44.833 --> 03:46.269
they'll wipe out
the whole colony.

03:46.269 --> 03:47.923
What are you gonna
do with them?

03:47.923 --> 03:49.359
Well, that's between
me and them,

03:49.359 --> 03:50.404
if you don't mind.

03:51.579 --> 03:52.623
That's okay.

03:53.450 --> 03:54.886
I understand these things.

03:57.280 --> 03:59.108
[EXHALES]
I just wanted to thank you

04:00.805 --> 04:02.067
for putting up with me,

04:03.721 --> 04:05.114
and all of my bees.

04:05.854 --> 04:08.030
This place was crabgrass
and weeds,

04:08.030 --> 04:09.249
and you brought it
back to life.

04:10.467 --> 04:11.555
You're a blessing.

04:13.209 --> 04:15.080
No one's ever
taken care of me before.

04:20.956 --> 04:22.000
I'll, uh...

04:24.307 --> 04:25.482
Mr. Clay...

04:28.920 --> 04:30.966
Come back at suppertime.
Let me feed you.

04:37.320 --> 04:39.366
- [SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]
- [HORNETS BUZZING]

04:47.548 --> 04:49.071
[TUBE LIGHT SHATTERS]

04:54.946 --> 04:56.034
[TASER STOPS BUZZING]

04:56.034 --> 04:58.080
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

05:09.483 --> 05:11.615
[BEES BUZZING]

05:19.928 --> 05:22.365
[MUSIC FADES OUT]

05:27.022 --> 05:28.980
[ALERT BEEPING]

05:35.813 --> 05:37.598
[GROANS]

05:39.251 --> 05:40.644
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Boss.

05:40.644 --> 05:42.124
- MAN: You got something, yeah?
- I got one.

05:42.124 --> 05:44.039
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- I want it. I need it.

05:44.039 --> 05:45.519
Hey, put it in my ear.

05:45.519 --> 05:48.348
Get this fucking
hippie shit down, please.

05:48.348 --> 05:50.045
- [COMPUTER BEEPS]
- [LINE CONNECTS]

05:50.045 --> 05:52.221
United Data Group.
Good afternoon. This is Boyd.

05:52.221 --> 05:53.265
How may I help you?

05:53.744 --> 05:55.137
Boyd.

05:55.137 --> 05:57.357
Uh, hello.
I just got a message saying

05:57.357 --> 05:59.359
that there's a problem
with my computer.

05:59.359 --> 06:01.143
<i>Don't you worry.
The message you received</i>

06:01.143 --> 06:03.363
<i>is from our United Data Group
antivirus software.</i>

06:03.363 --> 06:04.929
<i>It's part of
the software package</i>

06:04.929 --> 06:06.061
<i>that you pre-installed
on your computer.</i>

06:06.670 --> 06:08.716
I'm sorry.
I'm not a computer person.

06:08.716 --> 06:10.718
What did you say the name
of your product is again?

06:11.632 --> 06:13.677
[BEES BUZZING]

06:17.551 --> 06:20.162
Now, our records show
that you actually

06:20.162 --> 06:22.033
have an older version
on your account.

06:22.033 --> 06:24.645
So what I'm going to need you
to do is uninstall that

06:24.645 --> 06:26.429
<i>and install
the latest version.</i>

06:26.429 --> 06:28.344
Well, I have no idea
how to do that.

06:28.344 --> 06:29.911
My daughter set up
everything for me.

06:29.911 --> 06:31.521
<i>Well, I would recommend</i>

06:31.521 --> 06:32.870
<i>you take your computer
to an IT specialist.</i>

06:32.870 --> 06:34.437
However, keep in mind

06:34.437 --> 06:36.439
that you will lose
all your data,

06:36.439 --> 06:38.702
since they'll have to replace
the hard drive.

06:40.138 --> 06:41.488
I'm pretty remote out here.

06:43.751 --> 06:45.492
Everything I have
is on the computer.

06:45.492 --> 06:47.102
<i>Okay. There is actually</i>

06:47.102 --> 06:48.843
<i>a software package
that you can download</i>

06:48.843 --> 06:51.149
that would allow me
to reinstall remotely.

06:51.149 --> 06:54.152
All right. [SIGHS]
Tell me what to do.

06:54.631 --> 06:57.025
It's okay. Can you, uh,
can you type this,

06:57.025 --> 07:00.071
Friendly friend dot net?

07:00.071 --> 07:02.160
<i>Spelled just how it sounds.</i>

07:02.160 --> 07:03.771
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

07:03.771 --> 07:05.033
Okay. I'm there.

07:05.033 --> 07:06.469
And there should be a button

07:06.469 --> 07:07.557
on your screen
that says "install."

07:07.557 --> 07:08.906
<i>Can you click on that button?</i>

07:08.906 --> 07:10.778
- [MOUSE CLICKS]
- I clicked the button.

07:10.778 --> 07:12.040
So you're about
to see some windows

07:12.040 --> 07:13.520
open, close on your desktop,

07:13.520 --> 07:15.609
<i>as I reinstall
the virus shield for you.</i>

07:15.609 --> 07:17.045
[LINE MUTES]

07:17.480 --> 07:18.655
Okay.

07:19.003 --> 07:20.744
I hope you fucking clowns
are paying attention.

07:20.744 --> 07:21.963
You stick to the script,

07:22.442 --> 07:26.620
but not so much that you sound
like a goddamn robot.

07:26.620 --> 07:27.838
- All right?
- [BOYD LAUGHS]

07:27.838 --> 07:30.537
BOYD: She has got
10K checking,

07:30.537 --> 07:33.453
life insurance annuity,
Roth IRA,

07:33.453 --> 07:34.715
teacher's pension and...

07:34.715 --> 07:37.326
Holy fucking shit!

07:37.326 --> 07:39.154
- [SCATTERED LAUGHS]
- [CHUCKLING] All right.

07:39.154 --> 07:41.286
She is a signatory

07:41.286 --> 07:44.333
on a $2 million dollar
account.

07:44.333 --> 07:47.467
Some, uh...
It's some fucking charity.

07:47.467 --> 07:50.861
All right, kids,
let the strip mining begin.

07:50.861 --> 07:53.081
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

07:53.081 --> 07:54.648
Ooh.
My computer's going crazy.

07:54.648 --> 07:56.519
<i>Totally normal.</i>

07:56.519 --> 07:57.781
<i>Just do not touch
your keyboard.</i>

07:58.434 --> 07:59.827
[BEES BUZZING]

08:05.006 --> 08:06.529
Because of this inconvenience,

08:06.529 --> 08:08.009
I'm going to credit back
your subscription fees.

08:08.009 --> 08:09.184
How about that?

08:09.184 --> 08:11.360
I've gone ahead
and deposited $500

08:11.360 --> 08:13.275
into the account ending 020.

08:13.797 --> 08:15.538
Oh, that's not my account.

08:15.538 --> 08:17.279
That's an account
that I manage.

08:17.279 --> 08:18.759
Can you log into that account

08:18.759 --> 08:20.543
and verify the transfer,
please, Miss Parker?

08:20.543 --> 08:22.066
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

08:22.066 --> 08:24.460
Just hold on.

08:24.460 --> 08:26.288
[EXHALES] Yes, there's...

08:27.898 --> 08:30.553
There's a transfer
for $50,000?

08:30.553 --> 08:32.163
[LINE MUTES]

08:32.163 --> 08:35.558
- Set the hook with sympathy.
- [MAN LAUGHS]

08:35.558 --> 08:37.168
- [LINE UNMUTES]
- Miss Parker, I...

08:38.126 --> 08:39.562
I made a terrible mistake.

08:39.562 --> 08:41.085
<i>I was supposed
to credit you 500,</i>

08:41.085 --> 08:42.913
<i>but I don't know,
I got a stuck key here.</i>

08:44.001 --> 08:45.263
<i>I'm gonna lose my job here.</i>

08:46.221 --> 08:48.092
- I got kids.
- [LINE MUTES]

08:48.092 --> 08:49.441
I ain't got fucking kids.

08:49.441 --> 08:50.878
[SCATTERED LAUGHS]

08:50.878 --> 08:53.533
Oh, I don't want you
to get in trouble, but...

08:53.533 --> 08:57.624
[SIGHS]
I could wire the amount back.

08:57.624 --> 09:01.497
I will need
a different password though.

09:01.497 --> 09:02.933
One second.

09:02.933 --> 09:06.154
This is the master password
for all her accounts.

09:06.633 --> 09:11.159
Okay, so the second we get it,
we zero out everything.

09:11.159 --> 09:13.161
Um...

09:15.729 --> 09:17.600
You know, I, um...

09:18.383 --> 09:21.648
I think
I should call the bank. Hm?

09:22.083 --> 09:23.388
<i>You know what?
You're probably right.</i>

09:23.388 --> 09:26.000
But there goes my job,

09:26.522 --> 09:29.307
and there goes all your data.

09:32.310 --> 09:33.355
[SIGHS]

09:33.355 --> 09:34.922
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

09:34.922 --> 09:39.970
[SIGHS] All my kids' pictures
are on this computer.

09:43.365 --> 09:44.584
- [KEYBOARD CLACKS]
- Okay.

09:46.063 --> 09:47.325
[LAPTOP SHUTS DOWN]

09:47.325 --> 09:48.588
[DISEMBODIED
CASH REGISTER DINGS]

09:48.588 --> 09:49.676
[HORN BLOWS]

09:49.676 --> 09:51.286
Boom! Fucking yes!

09:51.286 --> 09:53.941
That is what
I am talking about! Come on!

09:53.941 --> 09:55.072
[ALL CHEERING]

09:55.595 --> 09:58.075
Let me fucking hear it!
I fucking love you people!

09:58.075 --> 09:59.424
I fucking love you!

09:59.424 --> 10:01.426
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

10:03.646 --> 10:04.734
Hello?

10:05.126 --> 10:06.693
Hello? You still there?

10:07.694 --> 10:09.609
[LAPTOP CHIMES]

10:15.223 --> 10:16.572
Uh-oh.

10:19.662 --> 10:21.925
- Oh.
- [KEYBOARD CLACKS]

10:28.105 --> 10:29.280
Oh.

10:33.197 --> 10:34.677
[CELL PHONE CHIMING]

10:39.203 --> 10:41.379
[CELL PHONE CONTINUES CHIMING]

10:44.426 --> 10:45.688
[SOBS]

10:47.690 --> 10:48.996
What did I do?

10:49.866 --> 10:51.868
Stupid... [INHALES]

10:51.868 --> 10:53.348
[MUSIC FADES OUT]

11:05.403 --> 11:07.101
[LID CLATTERING]

11:21.681 --> 11:23.770
[FIRE ALARM BEEPING]

11:29.689 --> 11:31.691
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

11:33.518 --> 11:34.737
Mrs. Parker?

11:34.737 --> 11:36.696
[FIRE ALARM CONTINUES BEEPING]

11:57.673 --> 11:58.848
[EXHALES]

11:59.719 --> 12:00.981
Don't move.

12:01.721 --> 12:03.723
Don't you fucking move.

12:04.593 --> 12:05.637
Drop the knife.

12:07.291 --> 12:08.553
[KNIFE CLATTERS]

12:09.554 --> 12:10.773
Hands behind your back.

12:14.472 --> 12:17.649
Slowly get on your knees
one knee at a time.

12:23.525 --> 12:26.789
- Now, who the fuck are you...
- [HANDCUFFS CLATTERING]

12:26.789 --> 12:28.922
...and what are you doing
in my mother's house?

12:28.922 --> 12:30.924
[HANDCUFFS CLICKING]

12:32.186 --> 12:33.230
Verona...

12:34.971 --> 12:36.059
I'm so sorry.

12:36.886 --> 12:38.061
How do you know my...

12:38.714 --> 12:40.672
[VERONA SHUDDERING]

12:40.672 --> 12:42.283
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

12:42.283 --> 12:43.719
Mom. [GASPS]

12:46.461 --> 12:47.810
[VERONA BREATHING HEAVILY]

12:47.810 --> 12:49.594
[INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

12:49.594 --> 12:51.683
AGENT: <i>Until we can clear him,
he's our best and only perp.</i>

12:51.683 --> 12:53.120
Clear him?

12:53.120 --> 12:54.512
Agent Parker,
I know that's your mother.

12:54.512 --> 12:55.557
I understand.

12:56.036 --> 12:58.995
But there's a world where
she committed suicide.

13:02.782 --> 13:06.089
Suicide? You can't be serious.

13:06.089 --> 13:09.745
That woman loved life
more than anybody I know.

13:09.745 --> 13:11.965
But by all means,
let's just completely ignore

13:11.965 --> 13:14.010
the big white dude
in her house with a knife.

13:14.010 --> 13:15.185
Get him up.

13:15.838 --> 13:16.796
Come on.

13:21.148 --> 13:22.410
AGENT 2: It's Clay, right?

13:23.106 --> 13:24.064
Adam Clay?

13:24.847 --> 13:26.762
I don't have much to say.

13:26.762 --> 13:28.285
Mr. Clay, we just got
a couple of questions.

13:28.285 --> 13:29.591
Like, what the fuck
were you doing

13:29.591 --> 13:30.853
in my mother's house?

13:31.680 --> 13:33.464
I was bringing her
a jar of honey.

13:35.205 --> 13:36.250
A jar of honey.

13:37.381 --> 13:38.513
Who the fuck are you?
Winnie-the-Pooh?

13:39.340 --> 13:40.471
I keep bees.

13:40.907 --> 13:42.256
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

13:42.256 --> 13:43.692
How do you know my mother?

13:44.606 --> 13:46.477
I rent some space
in the barn from her.

13:47.435 --> 13:48.653
I have a signed lease.

13:49.437 --> 13:52.744
But what the fuck
were you doing in her house?

13:55.095 --> 13:56.705
She didn't answer
when I knocked.

13:56.705 --> 13:58.011
I noted her car
in the driveway.

13:58.750 --> 14:00.361
I heard the smoke alarm
and I entered.

14:00.752 --> 14:02.232
You "noted"?

14:02.885 --> 14:04.278
You got a law enforcement
background?

14:04.974 --> 14:06.889
I told you,
I take care of bees.

14:22.296 --> 14:24.341
- [CAR DOOR SHUTS]
- [ENGINE STARTS]

14:24.907 --> 14:27.040
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING]

14:44.840 --> 14:46.973
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

14:52.282 --> 14:53.544
Oh, my God.

14:56.373 --> 14:58.419
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

15:10.170 --> 15:12.172
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

15:12.607 --> 15:13.782
[SNIFFLES]

15:16.959 --> 15:19.222
AGENT 2: His hands tested
negative for gunshot residue.

15:19.875 --> 15:21.703
But the prints on the gun
were your mother's.

15:22.834 --> 15:24.924
It seems, sadly,
it was suicide.

15:35.543 --> 15:38.720
Mr. Clay, I need to apologize
for last night.

15:40.026 --> 15:42.289
I realize I may have been
a little aggressive.

15:45.857 --> 15:47.381
That's understandable.

15:51.211 --> 15:53.256
Could I interest you
in something a bit stronger?

15:55.780 --> 15:56.825
No.

15:58.305 --> 15:59.828
But I'll sit with you
if you like.

16:07.009 --> 16:07.967
No, thank you.

16:12.536 --> 16:13.537
I wanted to thank you

16:15.017 --> 16:16.366
for taking care of my mom.

16:18.542 --> 16:21.067
I tried to stay in her life
as much as I could.

16:21.067 --> 16:22.590
Obviously, I could have
done a better job.

16:25.810 --> 16:27.377
Being old
can be a lonely thing.

16:29.336 --> 16:32.992
Turn a certain age, you cease
to exist. Cease to matter.

16:33.644 --> 16:36.430
Used to be a part of life,
of the family.

16:37.387 --> 16:39.215
Part of the hive,
I guess you could say.

16:41.609 --> 16:43.915
There's some British Isles
hiding in your accent.

16:46.701 --> 16:47.876
I was born there.

16:50.792 --> 16:52.750
I hated that she was
out here alone.

16:54.622 --> 16:55.797
She wouldn't leave.

16:56.885 --> 16:59.018
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

16:59.018 --> 17:00.236
There's too many memories.

17:03.848 --> 17:05.763
You know, I think I know
why she liked you.

17:06.764 --> 17:07.939
You're just like my brother.

17:09.593 --> 17:11.465
He was in MARSOC,
a Marine Raider.

17:12.335 --> 17:14.946
He was killed
a few years ago kicking doors.

17:16.252 --> 17:18.863
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
She loved him.

17:20.082 --> 17:21.605
He'd mow the lawn

17:21.605 --> 17:24.565
and you'd think
he invented fire. [CHUCKLES]

17:24.565 --> 17:26.567
You know, while I graduated
the FBI Academy

17:26.567 --> 17:28.743
and she said,
"Oh, that's nice."

17:31.876 --> 17:33.008
She got scammed.

17:34.879 --> 17:36.968
Somebody emptied out
all her accounts,

17:37.926 --> 17:39.754
her savings, her retirement.

17:39.754 --> 17:42.757
Got every penny.
Maxed out all her cards.

17:42.757 --> 17:44.672
She was an educator,

17:44.672 --> 17:46.674
director of a charity
for kids.

17:47.631 --> 17:49.372
They got two million
out of that account.

17:51.853 --> 17:53.637
- You know who did it?
- [SIGHS]

17:53.637 --> 17:55.422
I talked to an agent
in our cyber-crimes office.

17:56.162 --> 17:57.685
This crew's been operating
for two years

17:57.685 --> 17:58.990
and we don't even have names.

17:59.687 --> 18:01.428
And even if we did, good luck
building an indictment

18:01.428 --> 18:02.646
that would stand up in court.

18:03.343 --> 18:05.084
Some defense attorney
would just argue that

18:05.780 --> 18:07.347
the elderly victim agreed

18:07.825 --> 18:09.653
to wire a complete stranger
his entire life savings.

18:10.828 --> 18:12.221
Taking from an elderly person

18:12.221 --> 18:13.788
is as bad as stealing
from a child.

18:15.659 --> 18:16.965
Maybe worse.

18:16.965 --> 18:18.793
Someone hurts a child,

18:20.142 --> 18:21.317
there are parents.

18:22.144 --> 18:24.059
People who care,
ready to step in.

18:25.626 --> 18:27.323
Someone hurts
an older person...

18:29.456 --> 18:32.023
sometimes they're left to face
the hornets alone.

18:34.591 --> 18:36.115
Because either
it goes unnoticed...

18:38.769 --> 18:39.988
or no one cares.

18:41.511 --> 18:42.730
I care.

18:44.471 --> 18:45.733
And I'm stubborn.

18:47.038 --> 18:48.257
And so help me God,

18:48.649 --> 18:50.694
I'm going to get these
motherfuckers who did this.

18:56.657 --> 18:58.441
I need to take care
of the hive.

18:59.790 --> 19:01.444
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

19:01.444 --> 19:02.793
You've been up all night.

19:03.620 --> 19:05.361
CLAY: The hive
is more important.

19:06.014 --> 19:08.190
[DRAMATIC MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING]

19:18.374 --> 19:19.680
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

19:19.680 --> 19:21.943
[LINE RINGS, CONNECTS]

19:21.943 --> 19:23.553
What are you doing?

19:23.553 --> 19:25.512
- I thought you retired.
<i>- </i>  CLAY: <i>I did.</i>

19:26.730 --> 19:27.905
I need a favor.

19:28.384 --> 19:29.603
<i>What kind of favor?</i>

19:30.299 --> 19:32.258
A name and address.

19:32.910 --> 19:35.086
<i>- Easy.</i>
- Not easy.

19:36.392 --> 19:38.742
Even the FBI can't
find these people.

19:39.526 --> 19:40.962
Well, we're not the FBI,
are we?

19:40.962 --> 19:42.703
<i>Shoot me the deets
and stand by.</i>

19:45.184 --> 19:46.359
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

19:49.275 --> 19:50.711
Yeah.

19:50.711 --> 19:52.191
You weren't kidding.
This one kicked my butt.

19:52.669 --> 19:54.062
They're routing
all over the world.

19:54.062 --> 19:55.411
But you found them?

19:55.411 --> 19:57.370
Sure.
But who are these people?

19:58.414 --> 19:59.894
I'm gonna find out.

20:05.204 --> 20:06.683
GUARD: Whoa, whoa, whoa!

20:06.683 --> 20:08.337
The hell you think
you're going, pal?

20:08.903 --> 20:10.339
This United Data Group?

20:10.339 --> 20:11.732
Don't know nothing about that.

20:12.254 --> 20:14.865
This is private property,
and you're trespassing.

20:14.865 --> 20:16.127
I'm going inside.

20:17.303 --> 20:18.652
I'm going to burn it down.

20:19.479 --> 20:20.915
Yeah, that's not happening, buddy.

20:20.915 --> 20:22.438
You're not going
any-fucking-where

20:22.438 --> 20:24.397
except right the fuck back
the way you came.

20:24.397 --> 20:26.225
Do you know what they do here?

20:27.356 --> 20:29.228
Buddy, I'm counting to three.

20:29.837 --> 20:31.578
One, two, three.

