50:41.690 --> 50:43.170
is like our good friend
Adam Clay.

50:45.607 --> 50:47.044
Do you know what's that way?

50:48.088 --> 50:50.699
- Springfield...
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

50:50.699 --> 50:52.571
...where the call center
was torched.

50:53.876 --> 50:55.617
And that way
where Adam Clay's headed?

50:57.619 --> 50:58.707
Boston.

50:59.708 --> 51:00.840
Let's go.

51:02.755 --> 51:03.886
WILEY: Thank you.

51:10.458 --> 51:12.373
- [GUN CLICKING]
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]

51:17.944 --> 51:19.119
[MAN LAUGHS]

51:19.119 --> 51:20.338
How are you, my friend?

51:20.338 --> 51:22.253
- Good to see you, sir.
- Good to see you.

51:22.253 --> 51:24.516
- [MEN LAUGHING]
- WALLACE: Yeah, come on,

51:24.516 --> 51:25.995
leave them alone.
Leave them alone.

51:25.995 --> 51:27.736
Don't play with those things.
They go off.

51:27.736 --> 51:29.347
Sit down.
Make yourself comfortable.

51:32.263 --> 51:34.830
When I was sworn in
as director,

51:35.875 --> 51:39.270
I was read into programs
I never imagined existed.

51:39.270 --> 51:41.402
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

51:41.402 --> 51:42.621
Well...

51:44.188 --> 51:48.844
there are programs
even I wasn't privy to.

51:50.455 --> 51:52.021
Like the Beekeepers.

51:53.893 --> 51:57.026
The honeybee has always

51:57.026 --> 51:59.116
had a special relationship
with humanity.

51:59.116 --> 52:00.639
A sacred relationship.

52:01.553 --> 52:04.251
Why? No bees, no agriculture.

52:04.251 --> 52:06.427
No agriculture,
no civilization.

52:06.949 --> 52:10.736
Our nation is not
unlike a beehive,

52:10.736 --> 52:13.913
with its complex systems
of workers,

52:13.913 --> 52:15.915
caretakers, even royalty.

52:15.915 --> 52:20.049
If any of the beehive's
complex mechanisms

52:20.049 --> 52:21.181
are compromised,

52:21.921 --> 52:24.141
the hive collapses.

52:25.490 --> 52:27.187
Someone
a long time ago decided

52:27.187 --> 52:29.407
that a mechanism was needed

52:29.407 --> 52:30.886
to keep our nation safe.

52:30.886 --> 52:33.454
A mechanism
outside the chain of command,

52:33.454 --> 52:36.065
outside the system.

52:37.023 --> 52:41.941
Its one mission,
to keep the system safe.

52:42.594 --> 52:45.684
Beekeepers are given
all resources,

52:45.684 --> 52:49.905
empowered to act
on their own judgment.

52:49.905 --> 52:52.386
For decades,
they have quietly worked

52:52.386 --> 52:54.649
to keep the hive safe.

52:55.694 --> 52:58.044
That is, until now.

52:59.393 --> 53:02.266
It appears
that a retired Beekeeper

53:02.266 --> 53:03.658
has gone off program

53:03.658 --> 53:06.661
and is acting
in what he mistakenly believes

53:06.661 --> 53:09.055
is the hive's best interest.

53:10.230 --> 53:11.536
MAN: Can't somebody just
